The wife waited more than 15 minutes just to find out her food could not be made because they were out of whatever ingredients they needed to complete the order (likely the jack-fruit). To her surprise she learned that many other of the entrees were not available as well and this was 6pm on a Sunday (in a store that operates 11am to 10pm schedule. The dish she ordered to replace her first was the Buddha Bowl. Which came out like someone couldn't follow the cooking and arrangement instructions.  The sweet potatoes were poorly chopped. They were also missing the teriyaki sauce which was placed on the mushrooms.  The bowl had emanated a sour aroma in its take-out container (we ordered to-go). Which it is quite possible it was coming from the sweet potatoes since my wife choose to not eat them.  Also, the blondie brownie I ordered had been sitting for too long and became dry. I'm not sure if their deserts are refrigerated or rotated properly when on display like ALL OTHER LOCATIONS.  Also, on the same day from another visitor that is family the vegetables he had for his Soul bowl went uncooked. Seriously how does a fry cook not be able to tell when vegetables are cooked when the easiest indicator is its texture and color?  Nevertheless this was strike out number 5 when it comes to dining AT THIS LOCATION.  There's 4 other incidents that I didn't feel like I need to voice any concern. Yet, since this is consistently happening over the span of the year it seems like I will need to elaborate on every incident I have which is just about every visit. It feels like Native Foods is paying people to sabotage their own restaurant and brand.  I will be voicing my concern on social media and contacting NF directly.  - HOW DOES SOMEONE NOT KNOW HOW TO CHOP SWEET POTATOES - HOW DOES THE WEEKEND CREW NOT KNOW HOW TO COMMUNICATE OR MAKE A CALL WHEN THEY'RE RUNNING OUT OF INGREDIENTS. - WHY DOES IT TAKE SO LONG TO COOK MEALS WHEN YOU DON'T HAVE MANY PATRONS IN THE RESTAURANT OR A LOW VOLUME OF ONLINE ORDERS.  Just sit down at Majani's and watch how they work. SO MANY OF THESE ISSUES CAN BE ADDRESSED.

Why have I waited to eat here?! It’s soooo good!  First, I love they have an app for their loyalty club and when you first sign up it’s automatically $5/off your meal! Then every 100 points you get $5/off. You can also order from the app so it will be ready (takeout or dine in) and they do delivery through a few services.  Second, the food is superb, even my carnivore family loves eating here! My favorite is the lemongrass broccoli, it’s addicting and I never have liked broccoli. My mom likes the vegan fried chicken wings, they are strips really, but seasoned very well. The cupcakes are yummy too, I love the caramel carrot cake  cupcake. For drinks you can’t go wrong with the lavender lemonade but they have other flavored fresh teas and kombucha bottles too.  Third, location is great. Right down the street from Harper Theater so perfect for before/after movie dining and you can use the Harper parking garage on 53rd to access it immediately. They also have 15 minute parking on the street for quick take away.  Last (but maybe this should be first) it’s all GMO free, plant-based, chef crafted (even their meat replacements!) goodness!  The menu is huge, have fun trying everything- you can’t go wrong! My new favorite is the bulgogi bowl.

It was busy , but I quietly made my way to the front and was met by Marquies Haynes the General Manager who observed the one bite from half the sandwich and heard my explanation about how the sauce flavor was overwhelming; Mr. Haynes looked at me and said," I can see if it was something we did, but yea we can't exchange it for anything." I was disappointed, but in shock that he offered no concessions and basically smerked as I walked away per the observation of dinner party. I slide the sandwich back to Mr. Marquies Haynes and said, " I do not like to toss food, so can you toss that," Mr. Haynes said ok.  It is about quality customer service and this General Manager had no customer service skills. I am always at Native Foods, but maybe it is time for a break!  Thanks for reading!
Excellent for what it is, but make sure you’ve thoroughly reviewed the menu before going. I probably won’t return.
Great food
Good food and good people. I enjoyed this place very much!!!!
OMG...The Chicken & Waffles!!!!!!
Food always cold or they messing up my order,  I wish they had a negative star rating system cause they don't deserve the one I'm giving
Love native foods good customer service, great menu, clear atmosphere, reasonable prices, good location!
The food is great but the service is extra slow. I' ve been in line for a pick up for 11 mins now. People are actually leaving line now.

The trainee gave away my call ahead order however,  the cashier quickly made amends. She apologized for the inconvenience and offered me a drink and dessert for my time.  I appreciated her excellent customer service.  Thank you,  Taneishia :)
This place is a nice mix between plant-based food and plant processed food. Great lunch spot
Visiting from Cleveland, I'm blown away! Been there every day trying out everything I can on the menu before I leave in a couple days... so far so good! So wish we had this place back home
Vegan grub that's fresh, tasty, and satisfying.  Bonus: they seem to avoid soy and relish seasoning.  The sweets are positively sinful. Always a winner!
Good food, good atmosphere but not as good as Majani's on 71st.
Best watermelon mint drink I've ever had, I don't like it too heavy on the mint, they make it and everything amazing, love that chickn bacn avo!
I'm not Vegan. Still loved the food!
One of my all-time favorite places to be. A great and exciting menu if you enjoy eating vegetarian or vegan. So nice to have many tasty options. The staff here is great.
I'm a diner who must stick to gluten-free offerings. The staff gladly guided me to menu options that fit my needs and tasted great. Oh, and the lavender lemonade...

Truly delicious dining experience! Comfortable, cheery atmosphere. Very friendly, knowledgeable, accommodating personnel. Ample portions at reasonable prices. Had the Soul Bowl takeout; well seasoned, crisp vegetables topped brown rice, red beans & collards, with breaded seasoned seitan chicken strips. Served with ranch dressing & BarBQ sauce for dipping, cornbread on the side. A meal unto itself. On street metered parking, with longer term lot couple blocks away. In busy Hyde Park shopping area. Conveniently located.

I went into native foods today and ordered nachos with guacamole and one of their delicious oatmeal cream pies!!! They taste so good. The food is delicious but the service here is less than acceptable. The cashier today gave pretty good service. The gentleman checking the lobby and giving guest their food was terrible. The kitchen staff was okay i suppose. The experience was fine until i noticed after 30 minutes of waiting i didn't receive my nachos. Nor was i checked on by the lobby person at all. I'm not sure if they take the numbered displays off your table when you recieve your order but doing that would've helped very much with the lobby employee knowing if all was well or not. I arrived at 12:06 and when i noticed i was still waiting i got up to inform the cashier of my dilemma. She wasn't extremely apologetic but i appreciated her solution oriented attitude and offered to remake my nachos. I said sure. I was still pretty hungry and so when she asked if i wanted to keep the original order i said sure but 10 mintues later i still hadn't recieved the new order either. I couldn't wait anymore and just counted my loses but i realized i was a bit disappointed with the experience. It was below even mediocre. I wasn't treated like someone whose business was improtant. For that i won't be back to this location for a while. Much luck to everyone there nonetheless.
Delicious and healthy
Food is delicious!
Tasty vegan food but can sometimes take a while to get your order.
Service is so bad I threw away my "loyalty" card. I will not be back.
HORRIBLE SERVICE!!!!! It took 25 minutes for my food to be prepared. Then they had an attitude when I wanted a refund.

Amber and her Staff was great..... And gave me the Best Customer Service..... I truly enjoy eat at this Native Foods Cafe.... I always enjoy the food and The Great Service..... Thank U Angelica and Veta
Such a great vegan fast food joint! It's a chain and I definitely wish we had it where I live!
Great food and service. Almost didn't notice it was vegan
Great Wednesday deal... friendly staff and quick service!!!

Eating in here: great. Taking out: great. The peanut butter parfait is to die for.  However, do NOT get catering delivery from Native Foods. The company they use is either completely incompetent or a scam. The food came over half an hour late, and they couldn't even get in touch with the driver. This is the worst catering experience I've ever had.
Tasty vegan food even if your not a vegan and the food is always prepared on time

You won't have to worry about eating any animal DNA in this fine establishment. It is 100% vegan. The sandwiches are typically tasty although not always consistently great. It is a national chain or franchise, so it has the typical trappings of product displays and Picture menus.  The fruit drinks are pretty good , and they have beer - which is always nice.
So so good! Flavours are fantastic for everything at tried, even their custom freska teas
Good healthy, vegan-only food.
Native is a great place! Fast healthy food. Vegan. Everything here is delicious! Try the Lavender Lemonade!
Haven't tried anything I didn't like yet. Many of my carnivorous friends love Native Foods....the Nachos are deliciously awesome.  Every Burger is the bomb diggity!!!!!
They have a really great vegan and vegetarian menu. So many options to choose from. Definitely my go-to place.
Tables are sticky. The cups are spotty. Service is slow. If it weren't for the recipes shared among the chains, this place would be 2 stars at best.

I had no idea this was a vegan restaurant! I went the other day & ordered nacho's. Food was delicious, idk but maybe its known to some that it's vegan, but I wished I'd known then lol. Now I will have to go back.

New to the vegan lifestyle and having moved away from Chicago a few years ago finding a good vegan restaurant is hard. During our first visit we tried the "chicken" sandwich and wings. All I can say that this one some of the best food vegan or not that I've had in many years. The food was filling and fulfilling with portions that are good as well. I now hope to be back soon and will eventually work our way through the entire menu. The staff of friendly and seating area is clean and good for small groups. If you are in the area of this location try something different and hopefully you will find it as delicious as we did.

I was surprised to enjoy this place. You can't eat vegetarian food and accept the descriptions as-is; that is to say, don't eat their bacon and think it's *actually* bacon.  Flavors were good, portions were filling, location is easily accessible and parking is amply available.
The buffalo chicken tenders are soooooo delicious I love this place, my new go to!!!!

I am nowhere close to being Vegan. I love meat. But my boyfriend is a vegetarian and we were visiting Chicago for the first time ever. We couldn't find anywhere to eat (so many places close on Sunday!!) and ended up here.  To my surprise, I loved it. The fake meat tasted so good that I would definitely go here again. I wish they have Native Foods Cafe in Florida!! Branch to S. Florida guys!!
I had portobello burger great taste
Awesome mock meat options!

The Food. From Native foods is so very Healthy for the Heart ,Mind, and Soul ever since my Uncle Pastor John Jackson introduced good food that is good for the body certain levels that were some what high in my diet have dropped to Zero.: )

Delicious meat free menu. Some of the items sound like they may not taste that good but haven't disappointed by anything I've eaten here meat lover or vegan, you'll probably love at least one thing on the menu.

I love this place. This place has inspired me to be healthy and without the struggle. But they are really slow and usually have one register open - even when there is a line!!!!! That us unacceptable.

An interesting take on vegan food.  Always delicious the food errs toward imitating meat dishes with vegan alternatives.  There is often a "bacon cheeseburger" on the menu.  It doesn't really taste like that, but it is good none-the-less.
If you are vegan, this is great.  If not, its kind of expensive and oversold...
This place has delicious vegan food that can help you change your diet, or you can simply enjoy some vegan food. I recommend the chicken tenders with a side of chipotle sauce. Thank me later.
Really Good, I have found my new lunch spot!!

This is a great place for those who are transitioning to being vegan / vegetarian. The staff is  knowledgeable about the ingredients. There are posters explaining the vegan meat substitutes for chicken, burgers, tacos etc. I ordered the Sesame Seed Chicken Bites with steamed Kale. The portions sizes are pretty large so I ordered an appetizers instead of an entree. I also tried the Watermelon Fresca which has Agave Nectar for its sugar base. There are healthy options selections at this restaurants.
Awesome little hidden place. Obviously plenty of delicious vegetarian options, and a GREAT juice bar. They also serve beer, which is always a plus!
This is my favorite Native Foods because I like eating outside when it's nice out abs is nice and quiet. Try the Scorpion Burger if you've never tried it. It's the best.

Healthy, delicious food in large portions. What's not to love? I've been here twice and got the bowls both times. There's enough food in there for two meals, especially if you're a light eater like me. The bowls are delicious, with just the right proportion of flavor, and I never find myself missing meat here. Honestly, it doesn't even taste like it's vegan... but it is. They also have a fantastic rewards program, so be sure to check that out. The tables at this location get a little dirty sometimes, but this is something I gladly put up with.
Very nice place. Good food and really frriendly service.
I think these desserts are as fab and delicious if not more than the meals, sandwiches, soups etc! Guilt free eats!
The customer service is beyond phenomenal. You'll feel right at home!
The food is great the managers are rude and condescending. I refuse to go back.

A delicious, healthy food restaurant located in the middle of Hyde Park! Friendly staff, coupled with a lovely variety of drinks, food, and desserts, and a colorful yet rustic atmosphere make for an amazing experience!
love this place! i fell in love at first bite!

Fantastic food and service. Prices are good. This would be even better if they had a dining section for people that wish to make an extended experience out of it (servers, dishes at varying times, etc).
